First, let \(\angle CAB = 2\alpha\). Since \(AB = AC\), \(\angle ABC = \angle ACB = 90^\circ - \alpha\). The angle bisector of \(\angle CAB\) divides \(\angle CAB\) into two equal parts, so \(\angle CAD = \angle DAB = \alpha\). Similarly, the angle bisector of \(\angle ABC\) divides \(\angle ABC\) into two equal parts, so \(\angle ABE = \angle EBC = 45^\circ - \frac{\alpha}{2}\).

